    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-09-07T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-09-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="308"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d308">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/11751</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Diplomatic Agent at Cairo</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_GH1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gary</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 125</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Cairo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-09-07">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 7, 1918</hi>
                        </date>. <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received October 15.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: With further reference to the Department’s
                    telegraphic instruction of July 31, 4 p.m.,<note n="3" xml:id="d308fn3">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_295">p. 295</ref>.</note> and
                    to my despatch No. 116 of August 29, 1918,<note n="1" xml:id="d308fn2">Not
                        printed.</note> concerning the incident of the display of the American flag
                    by a Jewish battalion, I have the honor to enclose herewith a copy of a note
                    dated September 2, 1918,<note n="1" xml:id="d308fn1">Not printed.</note> which I
                    have received from the British High Commissioner wherein His Excellency informs
                    me that the commander-in-chief states that this misuse of the American flag was
                    entirely without authority and even without the knowledge of the commanding
                    officer of the battalion concerned.</p>
                <p>The High Commissioner conveys the regret of the commander-in-chief that this
                    incident should have occurred and states that <persName corresp="#p_AGEHH1"
                        >General Allenby</persName> wishes to assure me that steps have been taken
                    to prevent any occurrence of a similar nature in the future in Egypt or
                    Palestine.</p>
                <p>Immediately upon receipt of the High Commissioner’s note, I wrote thanking him
                    and asking him to be so good as to assure <persName corresp="#p_AGEHH1">General
                        Allenby</persName> of my sincere appreciation of his courteous message and
                    of the consideration he has shown in taking steps to prevent a recurrence of the
                    incident.</p>
                <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_GH1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Hampson Gary</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
